# Architecture

Stack: **Next.js 14 App Router**, **TypeScript strict**, **Supabase** (Auth/Postgres/Storage), **Drizzle** (schema only), **TanStack Query** (client reads), **Tailwind**.

## Layer map

```
Browser
  â†’ middleware.ts          session refresh + route guard (no business data)
  â†’ app/                   routes (Server Components default)
       layouts             requireRole + shell
       pages               initial data (server) or pass props to client
  â†’ components/            UI (client only when interactive)
  â†’ hooks/queries/         React Query hooks (client Supabase reads)
  â†’ lib/api/               client fetchers (called by hooks only)
  â†’ lib/queries/           server-side query loaders (RSC / actions)
  â†’ lib/auth.ts            getSessionUser, requireRole (React cache)
  â†’ lib/supabase/          client | server | middleware | admin
  â†’ types/                 centralized TypeScript (import @/types)
  â†’ db/schema.ts           Drizzle schema source of truth
```

## Role workspaces

| Prefix | Roles | Layout guard |
|--------|-------|--------------|
| `/driver/*` | driver, admin | `requireRole(["driver","admin"])` |
| `/agent/*` | agent, admin | `requireRole(["agent","admin"])` |
| `/admin/*` | admin | `requireRole(["admin"])` |

## Data fetching rules

| Context | Pattern |
|---------|---------|
| Server Component / layout / page | `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/server` + `lib/queries/*` |
| Server Action | `requireRole` / `requireRoleForAction` then server client |
| Client Component read | **React Query hook** in `hooks/queries/` â†’ fetcher in `lib/api/` |
| Client mutation | Server Action preferred; invalidate via `queryClient.invalidateQueries` |
| Admin bootstrap only | `createAdminClient()` â€” never in client code |

## Security

- Never expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` to the browser.
- Never bypass RLS except `/setup` and admin promotion flows.
- Privileged roles are never assigned via signup metadata.

## Performance defaults (already in codebase)

- `cache()` on `getSessionUser`, `getCurrentProfile`, `listProfilesForUser`, `requireActiveProfileSelection`.
- Lazy-load Recharts via `dynamic()` in chart wrappers.
- `loading.tsx` per role workspace for streaming skeletons.
- `Promise.all` for independent server queries.

## Before every change, verify

1. Does it belong in the correct layer (server vs client vs hook vs action)?
2. Does it respect role boundaries and existing auth flow?
3. Are types imported from `@/types`, not re-declared?
4. Does a new client Supabase read use React Query (not raw `useEffect`)?

Full reference: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
